  "prompt": "Can I apply for internet banking in Andhra bank without visiting the branch?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Andhra Bank was merged with Union Bank of India on April 1, 2020. After this merger, all Andhra Bank accounts were integrated into the Union Bank of India system. If you want to apply for internet banking, you would need to follow Union Bank of India's procedures for setting up online banking.\n\nTypically, many banks offer the option to apply for internet banking services online without visiting a branch. Here are the general steps you might follow:\n\n1. **Visit the Union Bank of India Website**: Go to the official website of Union Bank of India.\n\n2. **Internet Banking Section**: Look for the 'Internet Banking' or 'Digital Banking' section.\n\n3. **New User Registration**: Find an option like 'New User Registration' or 'Register Online'. This will direct you to a form where you can start the registration process.\n\n4. **Provide Details**: You may be asked to provide account details, customer information, and possibly a registered mobile number to verify your identity.\n\n5. **Set Up Security Details**: You will likely need to set up a user ID and password, as well as security questions.\n\n6. **Activation**: Some banks require you to download a form, fill it out, and submit it at a bank branch or upload it online for verification.\n\nSince procedures can change, it is best to visit Union Bank of India's official website or contact their customer support for the latest information and guidance tailored to your specific needs.",
